<raw><![CDATA[ BEIJING, Jan 14 (Reuters) - Maintaining a stable yuan isimportant to both the global and the Chinese economy, a foreignministry spokeswoman said on Thursday. Jiang Yu's comments, in response to a question about Europeancalls for a stronger yuan, were a reiteration of China'slong-standing defence of why it has held its exchange rate stablesince the worsening of the global financial crisis in mid-2008. The European Union's trade commissioner-designate Karel deGucht said in Brussels on Tuesday that China should revalue theyuan to ease global trade imbalances. (Reporting by Chris Buckley; Writing by Simon Rabinovitch;Editing by Ken Wills)             ]]></raw>
